Privacy Policy for PDF Scanner - Document Scanner
Last Updated: June 23, 2026

1. Introduction
PDF Scanner - Document Scanner ("the App") is committed to protecting your privacy. This Privacy Policy explains how we collect, use, and safeguard your information when you use our App.

2. Information We Collect
2.1 Device Information

Device ID and advertising ID (for ad personalization)
App version and usage statistics
Operating system version
Scan count (to determine when to show ads)
2.2 Data You Provide

Photos and images you select from your device gallery (for PDF conversion)
Documents you scan using the camera
User preferences (dark mode, onboarding status)
2.3 Automatically Collected Information

App usage patterns and crash reports
Ad interaction data (via Google AdMob)
3. How We Use Your Information
We use the collected information for the following purposes:

To provide and improve the App: Process scanned documents, convert images to PDF, and enable app features
To display advertisements: Show personalized ads via Google AdMob
To analyze usage: Understand how users interact with the App to improve features
To fix bugs: Crash reports help us identify and fix issues
4. Third-Party Services
Our App uses the following third-party services:

4.1 Google AdMob

Collects device ID and advertising ID for ad personalization
Displays ads within the App
Privacy Policy: https://policies.google.com/privacy
4.2 Google Play Services

Required for ML Kit Document Scanner and OCR features
Privacy Policy: https://policies.google.com/privacy
4.3 Google ML Kit

Processes documents locally on your device for edge detection and OCR
No data is sent to Google servers for document scanning
Privacy Policy: https://policies.google.com/privacy
4.4 uCrop

Image cropping library
Privacy Policy: https://github.com/Yalantis/uCrop
5. Data Storage and Security
Local Storage: All scanned documents and images are stored locally on your device
No Cloud Storage: We do not upload your documents to any cloud servers
Data Retention: Data is retained until you uninstall the App or manually delete documents
Security: We implement reasonable security measures to protect your information
6. Data Sharing
We do not sell, trade, or rent your personal information to third parties. We may share data with:

Service Providers: Google AdMob for ad delivery (as described above)
Legal Requirements: If required by law or to protect our rights
7. Your Rights
You have the right to:

Access: Request access to your personal data
Delete: Request deletion of your data (by uninstalling the App)
Opt-out: Disable personalized ads in your device settings
8. Children's Privacy
The App is not intended for children under 13. We do not knowingly collect personal information from children.

9. Changes to This Policy
We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. We will notify you of any changes by posting the new policy on this page.

